        "content_en": "Three critical points determine stability:\n• B = Center of buoyancy (center of underwater volume)\n• G = Center of gravity (center of all weight)\n• M = Metacenter (pivot point when tilting)\n\nStable: M is above G → vessel returns upright\nUnstable: M is below G → vessel capsizes!\n\nTo improve stability:\n• Keep heavy items LOW (lowers G)\n• Don't overload the deck (raises G)\n• Distribute weight evenly\n• Every person counts as 75 kg\n• Two children under 10 = 1 adult",
